What you need to know:

Reports from Japan say his employers Reysol are already in negotiations with Al Duhail who are ready to splash close to Sh1 billion to prise him away from the Chiba Prefecture-based sideOlunga, who earns about Sh85 million per year at Reysol, is also attracting interest from clubs from EuropeItalian news site Calciomercato has claimed that he could join a Serie A side in the current transfer window which opened on Monday